The paper discusses a testing framework for deep learning systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on ensuring reliability and robustness suggests a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect to the research. The use of adversarial inputs and neuron coverage also suggests a computer security (cs.CR) aspect. Finally, the empirical evaluations on well-known datasets suggest a computer vision (cs.CV) aspect to the research.
